<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1890-03-27T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1890-03-27T00:00:00-05:00" n="249" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d249">
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Blaine</persName> to Mr.
                                    <persName type="to">Hicks</persName>.</hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1890-03-27"><hi rend="italic">March 27,
                                1890</hi></date>.</dateline>
                            <seg rendition="#left">No. 43.]</seg></opener>
                        <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have received your No. 91, of the 21st
                            ultimo, relating to the claim of the Hydrographic Commission of the
                            Amazon against the Government of Peru. The claimants have been informed
                            of your action and have been told that you will continue to press their
                            claim.</p>
                        <p>I am, etc.,</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">James G. Blaine.</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>